New Records: Zack Wheeler achieved his 100th career win.
Key Match Events: Zack Wheeler pitched seven scoreless innings.
Edmundo Sosa and Trea Turner each hit home runs.
Philadelphia Phillies won 3-0 against Atlanta Braves.
Post-Match Reflections: Zack Wheeler expressed pride in achieving his 100th career win against the Braves.
Phillies manager Rob Thomson praised Wheeler's performance and mentioned his Cy Young candidacy.
Atlanta starter Max Fried acknowledged Wheeler's dominance.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The win pushed the Phillies' NL East lead over the Braves to six games.
Wheeler's performance lowered his ERA to 2.63, just behind Chris Sale's 2.58.
